  "body": "we agreed to make pin messages permanent so everybody who joins later can see them. The limit is 3 pinned messages per chat/channel. Here is the desktop design for it: \r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Mr3rqxxgKJ2zMQ06UAKiWL/%F0%9F%92%AC-Chat%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=6111%3A44054\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/120476285-12636c00-c3b3-11eb-8d2d-453db86d9795.png)\r\n\r\n**Expected behaviour:** \r\n\r\n1. admin in a group chat can Pin up to 3 messages\r\n2. admin in community can Pin up to 3 messages in community channel\r\n3. everyone in 1x1 chat can pin up to 3 messages in chat\r\n4. when trying to pin more than 3 messages -> show **Pin limit reached** message with wording `Unpin previous message first`\r\n5. when unpin any message , after that a  newly pinned one is added to the bottom of the list\r\n6. newcomers for a community or a group chat should also see there 3 pinned messages, which should be kept \"forever\" (no lifetime for messages, once pinned -> they stay there)\r\n\r\n",
